Subject: [PATCH] vlan: Fix reading memory beyond skb->tail in
 skb_vlan_tagged_multi
References: bnc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 4.16.6
Git-commit: 7ce2367254e84753bceb07327aaf5c953cfce117

[ Upstream commit 7ce2367254e84753bceb07327aaf5c953cfce117 ]

Syzkaller spotted an old bug which leads to reading skb beyond tail by 4
bytes on vlan tagged packets.
This is caused because skb_vlan_tagged_multi() did not check
skb_headlen.

